<tr><td colspan="2"><p align="justify">A K-Ar date of about 0.3 million years was obtained from a basaltic rock from Mago Island on the Lau Ridge (Cole et al., 1990).  Three scoria cones and short lava flows, some of which contain peridotite xenoliths, are located on the island.</p></td></tr>
