<tr><td colspan="2"><p align="justify">The smaller and younger of two coalescing shield volcanoes on Tahiti, Tahiti-Iti (Taiarapu) is connected to Tahiti-Nui by a narrow isthmus. Potassium-Argon ages range from 0.48-0.38 million years ago (Duncan and Mcdougall 1976).</p></td></tr>
