<tr><td colspan="2"><p align="justify">The Kawdy Metah volcanic field lies along the Kawdy Plateau north of Level Mountain and contains a group of tuyas and subglacial mounds of Pleistocene age (Hickson et al., 1994).      </p></td></tr>
