<tr><td colspan="2"><p align="justify">The isolated Sutter Buttes rise dramatically above the flat floor of the Sacramento Valley.  This andesitic-to-rhyolitic lava-dome complex was active during the Pleistocene.  An andesitic central core is surrounded by a ring of dacitic-to-rhyolitic domes.</p></td></tr>
