<tr><td colspan="2"><p align="justify">The Simcoe volcanic field, of Pliocene-to-Pleistocene age, lies east and SE of Mount Adams.  Small shield volcanoes and cinder cones, many erupted along N-S fissures, range in age to about 0.5 million years old.     </p></td></tr>
