<tr><td colspan="2"><p align="justify">Smelter Knolls in west-central Utah are a Pliocene rhyolitic lava dome complex.  Nearby basaltic volcanism is dated at 0.31 million years ago (Nash, in Wood and Kienle 1990).      </p></td></tr>
