<tr><td colspan="2"><p align="justify">The Willow Peak cinder cone is located in the White River National Forest, and can be reached from Coffee Pot Road. Although geomorphically young, this cone is regarded as somewhat older than the Dotsero lava flow (about 4,000 years before present). A lava flow that traveled 5.5 km to the east.</p></td></tr>
