<tr><td colspan="2"><p align="justify">The Pinzón Island shield volcano is covered with lava flows originating from a crater SW of the summit.  The most prominent feature is a small steep-walled 1-km-wide caldera NW of the summit.  Potassium-Argon dates range from 1.09 to 0.93 million years ago (Cox 1983).     </p></td></tr>
