<tr><td colspan="2"><p align="justify">Aguilera, located west of Lake Argentina and NE of Peel Fjiord, is one of a chain of poorly known volcanoes in the southernmost Chilean Andes. Geochemical evidence indicated that the dacitic volcano was the source of a major late-Holocene Patagonian tephra layer that was erupted less than about 3600 years ago.</p></td></tr>
