<tr><td colspan="2"><p align="justify">Melimoyu is a stratovolcano with an 8-km-wide, largely buried caldera located ~40 km NW of the town of Puyuhuapi.  The ice-filled caldera is drained by a glacier through a notch in the NE caldera rim.  The basaltic-andesite volcano is elongated 10 km in an E-W direction and has several cinder cones.  A 1-km-wide crater is located at its summit, and two late-Holocene tephra layers have been documented.</p></td></tr>
