<tr><td colspan="2"><p align="justify">The Plio-Pleistocene Llancanelo volcanic field lies west of the saline lake of the same name in the Mendoza province of Argentina. The field includes scoria cones, tuff cones, and tuff rings. Often described as covering an area of 10,700 km2, that zone includes the Cerro Nevado and Northern Mendoza volcanic fields.</p></td></tr>
