<tr><td colspan="2"><p align="justify">The andesitic stratovolcano Cerro Inacalari is located about 25 km SE of Cerro del Azufre along the Chile-Bolivia border. Satellite imagery shows a small lake in the 400-m-diameter summit crater. It's age was estimated by Gonzales-Ferron (1995) as Pliocene-Pleistocene.</p></td></tr>
