<tr><td colspan="2"><p align="justify">Laguna Verde, located west of Colachi volcano, is one of a cluster of young stratovolcanoes north and east of Lascar. Laguna Verde was considered to be of Pleistocene-Holocene age (González-Ferrán, 1995), but de Silva (pers. comm., 2007) indicated it was of probable Pleistocene age. The andesitic volcano collapsed to the north, producing a debris avalanche that dammed the Quebrada Portor, forming a lake.</p></td></tr>
