<tr><td colspan="2"><p align="justify">Morne Garu stratovolcano, south of Soufrière St. Vincent volcano was active during the Pleistocene.  A young Ar-Ar date of 0.011 +/- 0.014 suggests that activity may have overlapped with that of Soufrière St. Vincent volcano (Robertson, 2005b).</p></td></tr>
