<tr><td colspan="2"><p align="justify">The elongated N-S trending Kulal shield volcano east of the south end of Lake Turkana is mostly Pliocene in age, with parasitic cinder cones of probable Pleistocene age (Ochieng' et al. 1988).     </p></td></tr>
