<tr><td colspan="2"><p align="justify">The Bijar volcanic field of a cluster of Miocene dacitic and rhyolitic lava domes and a group of Pleistocene (Potassium-Argon dates 1.3-0.5 million years ago) alkaline cinder and spatter cones and two rhyolitic lava domes (Boccaletti et al. 1976-77).     </p></td></tr>
