<tr><td colspan="2"><p align="justify">Walker et al. (2009) dated basalts along the East Neh fault at 1.45-1.75, 1.69-1.79, and 4.71-4.91 Ma. Volcanic deposits are strung out along perhaps 50 km on either side of the fault.</p></td></tr>
