<tr><td colspan="2"><p align="justify">Very fresh-looking Quaternary basaltic lava flows have issued from vents within the Kuh-e Nader (Nader Mountains) between Taftan and Bazman volcanoes in SE Iran (Catalog of Active Volcanoes of the World). These flows, including some cones and craters, were erupted amongst a group of rugged Cretaceous limestone peaks.</p></td></tr>
