<tr><td colspan="2"><p align="justify">Rodriguez Island lies along the Rodriguez Fracture Zone about 650 km east of Mauritius Island.  The 18 x 6.5 km wide island is consists of a basaltic shield volcano of probably Plio-Pleistocene age.   K-Ar ages of 1.54 and 1.32 million years were obtained from lava flows (Upton et al., 1967).</p></td></tr>
