<tr><td colspan="2"><p align="justify">The Sarik center consists of two young andesitic/basaltic cones with vegetated, but uneroded surfaces. The andesitic-dacitic Gajah center, 10 km to the SW, consists of a single cone with a rubbly lava flow.  Both centers were considered to be of Pleistocene or Holocene age (Rock et al., 1983).</p></td></tr>
