<tr><td colspan="2"><p align="justify">Located in south-central Sumatra overlooking the Semalako Plain, Bukit Lumut has a 2.1-km-diameter crater open to the north. It was mapped by Budiardjo et al. (2001) as the Pleistocene 0.893 Ma Lumut Andesite. Two small hills within that unit, one of which is name Bukit Pabus, consist of the slightly older Pabus Tuff (0.895 Ma). The Hululais volcano and geothermal are lies immediately to the SE.</p></td></tr>
