<tr><td colspan="2"><p align="justify">Oetakeyama consists of a group of lava domes active from about 1.8 to 0.8 million years ago (Nakano et al., 2001-). Kano and Takarada (2007) noted late-Pliocene to early Pleistocene activity, including at the early Pleistocene Senyama pyroclastic cone north of the Oetakayama (O'e-Takayama). The latest activity noted was K-Ar dated at about 1.8-1.6 million years.</p></td></tr>
