<tr><td colspan="2"><p align="justify">Kamitakara (or Takara) volcano was the source of deposits forming the Kamitakara pyroclastic flow plateau.  The dacitic-to-rhyolitic deposits were erupted about 0.75 or 0.70 million years ago (Nakano et al., 2001-).  Ono et al. (1981) listed a Potassium-Argon date of  about 600,000 years.</p></td></tr>
