<tr><td colspan="2"><p align="justify">Mutsu-Hiuchidake, on the Shimokita Peninsula, is the northernmost volcano on the island of Honshu. The andesitic-dacitic stratovolcano is Pleistocene in age, with dated activity during an interval ranging from about 700,000 to 50,000 years ago, although fumarolic activity continues.</p></td></tr>
