<tr><td colspan="2"><p align="justify">Mt. Kerewa is a deeply dissected Pleistocene andesitic stratovolcano south of Doma Peaks.  A group of small cones, craters and domes is located to the west, and Mt. Ne is situated immediately to the NE (Mackenzie and Johnson 1984).     </p></td></tr>
