<tr><td colspan="2"><p align="justify">Tokachi-Mitsumata, a rhyolitic caldera that was the source of the Muka and Meto pyroclastic flows, was active about 0.6-0.3 million years ago (Nakano et al., 2001-).  Ishii et al. (2008) listed dates of around 1 million years ago for formation of the Tokachi-Mitsumata caldera.</p></td></tr>
