<tr><td colspan="2"><p align="justify">Mt. Hagen is comprised of three coalescing stratovolcanoes with NW-facing escarpments that may result from slope failure (Johnson 1987).  Potassium-Argon dates of 0.42 and 0.22 million years ago have been obtained  (Mackenzie and Johnson 1984).     </p></td></tr>
