<tr><td colspan="2"><p align="justify">The Pleistocene Ialibu stratovolcano is morphologically complex, with deeply eroded gorges and a major fault zone that cuts the entire edifice. In contrast to many other Highlands volcanoes, the most mafic basaltic rocks are topographically higher than andesitic rocks (Mackenzie and Johnson 1984).     </p></td></tr>
