<tr><td colspan="2"><p align="justify">Tabar Island, the southernmost of the Tabar island group, consists of two partially coalescing Pleistocene volcanoes connected by a low isthmus.  The younger, southern cone contains a 3-5 km wide depression breached to the SE.     </p></td></tr>
