<tr><td colspan="2"><p align="justify">Ded i Baba (Ded and Baba) is an early Pleistocene shield-like volcano SW of Koshelev volcano; an unnamed mid-Pleistocene volcano with a small caldera breached to the east lies between these two volcanoes (Masurenkov 1980).     </p></td></tr>
