<tr><td colspan="2"><p align="justify">Ozernoy is a small basaltic shield volcano considered early Holocene by Masurenkov (1980) NW of Ksudach. It has a volume of only 2 km3 and rises 300 m above the floor of a valley in the center of the southern Kamchatka Peninsula. This was not included by Ponomareva et al. (2007) in their review of Holocene volcanoes in Kamchatka.</p></td></tr>
