<tr><td colspan="2"><p align="justify">Piratkovsky, identified by Masurenkov (1980) as a mid-Pleistocene to Holocene stratovolcano with a small caldera, is  NE of Khodutka volcano. It partially overlaps Pleistocene volcanoes to the NW and lies at the eastern margin of the Quaternary volcanic chain of southern Kamchatka. This was not included by Ponomareva et al. (2007) in their review of Holocene volcanoes in Kamchatka.</p></td></tr>
