<tr><td colspan="2"><p align="justify">The Pliocene to Pleistocene Mbareke volcanic center consists of a core of basaltic andesite to andesite lavas and breccias overlain by a thick pile of olivine basalt lavas.  An andesitic plug lies on the southern rim of the dissected summit crater.     </p></td></tr>
