<tr><td colspan="2"><p align="justify">Anaun is a Quaternary basaltic stratovolcano NE of Uksichan in the southern Sredinny Range. A chain of NE-SW-trending cinder cones extends to the SW, and another chain of numerous cinder cones displays the same orientation S and SE of the volcano. Early geological studies in the Sredinny Range (Ogorodov et al., 1972) assigned Holocene ages based on morphology, but later work noted that these volcanoes appear younger because they have less tephra cover than those in eastern Kamchatka. Researchers such as Ponomareva et al. (2007) do not consider this volcano to be Holocene.</p></td></tr>
