<tr><td colspan="2"><p align="justify">Three small overlapping Quaternary basaltic to basaltic-andesite shield-like volcanoes are located NE of Leutongey volcano, west of the crest of the central Sredinny Range. Tuzovsky, the SW-most edifice, is the highest; Tvitunup is the northernmost, and Sredny is NE of Tuzovsky. Early geological studies in the Sredinny Range (Ogorodov et al., 1972) assigned Holocene ages based on morphology, but later work noted that these volcanoes appear younger because they have less tephra cover than those in eastern Kamchatka. Researchers such as Pevzner (2006) and Ponomareva et al. (2007) do not consider this volcano to be Holocene.</p></td></tr>
