<tr><td colspan="2"><p align="justify">Schmidt volcano is a large mid- to late-Pleistocene eroded shield-like volcano located N of Kronotsky volcano and SW of Gamchen (Lutchitsky, 1974). A dike complex is prominent along a NE-trending fault zone. Andreev et al. (1988) reported that following the cessation of Pleistocene activity, regional basaltic volcanism produced some monogenetic cinder cones on the E and NE flanks during the Holocene. However, Ponomareva et al. (2007) did not include this volcano as a Holocene center.</p></td></tr>
